e 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda was born in 1180, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with James Bisege. She died in 1250, in Baddesley Clinton, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1180–1250":"1180–1250","1184–1236":"1184–1236","1210–1238":"1210–1238","1210–1278":"1210–1278","–Male":"Surnud","1238":"1238","1236":"1236","1278":"1278","1210":"1210","1250":"1250","1184":"1184","6 May 1236":"6. mai 1236","1180":"1180","Ullesthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"Ullesthorpe, Leicestershire, England","Baddesley, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Baddesley Clinton, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Baddesley Clinton, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1180–1250":"1180–1250","1184–1236":"1184–1236","1210–1238":"1210–1238","1210–1278":"1210–1278","–Male":"Kuollut","1238":"1238","1236":"1236","1278":"1278","1210":"1210","1250":"1250","1184":"1184","6 May 1236":"6. toukokuuta 1236","1180":"1180","Ullesthorpe, Leicestershire, England":"Ullesthorpe, Leicestershire, England","Baddesley, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Baddesley Clinton, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Baddesley Clinton, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kunin